comment_data.body:
I'm wondering that this may be the cleanest / most_consistent solution for the two occasions when only `NameBuff` population is needed.

Other alternatives, similar to 
```
const char *get_appname(bool namelike, bool return_value_needed) {
    const char *env_val = os_getenv("NVIM_APPNAME");
    
    [add env val to NameBuff]
 
    if (return_value_needed) {
       return env_val;
    } else {
       // Potential xfree(env_val) here, so caller only needs to free if 
       // no return value is consumed
       return NULL;
    }
}
```
 just feel more confusing (signature, return value, potential side effects)... 
 
 In case there may be a straightforward, elegant solution in mind, I'm glad to go with your suggestion.

